@page "/electronics/lightbox"
<h3>Light Box</h3>

<h4>What is Light Box?</h4>
<div class="container" style="margin-right: 0; margin-left: 0;">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-8" style="padding-right: 0; padding-left: 0;">
            <p>Light Box is an electronics project that allows people to interact with a LED strip with some dials and a button to toggle programs, where they can change the colours that appear to the speed of sequeneces and even the LEDs that appear.</p>
            <p>The two main goals of this was to learn more about the electronics components and programming the board, and to make something that people could interact and play around with (where the fun is in disocvering and exploring what it can do).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
            <img src="images/lightbox/lightbox-rainbow-1.jpg" alt="" width="300px"/>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h4>Code</h4>
<p>Source Code available <BasicLink Text="here" Url="https://gist.github.com/ChrisWoody/4409806fbc3860d5780e14eb9f3f77a0"/>.</p>

<h4>Slideshow</h4>
@if (_displaySlideshow)
{
    <button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick=DisplaySlideshow>Hide slideshow</button>

    <div>
        <button class="btn btn-info" style="margin: 5px 5px 5px 0" @onclick=PreviousSlideshowItem>Previous</button>
        <button class="btn btn-info" style="margin: 5px 5px 5px 0" @onclick=NextSlideshowItem>Next</button>
    </div>

    <div style="text-align: center">
        <img src="@_imgUrls[_currentSlideShowItem]" alt="an image should be here..." width="70%"/>
    </div>
}
else
{
    <button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick=DisplaySlideshow>Show slideshow</button>
}

