<h4>Lessons Learned</h4>
<ul>
    <li>When soldering header pins to the Adafruit board, place the pins and board in a breadboard so the pins are vertically properly</li>
    <li>The 26 AWG crimper wasn't small enough for the headers/pins used, had to use pliers to finish off the crimping. Perhaps 28 AWG would work</li>
    <li>When plugging in the board via USB, Windows might report it has a faulty device. It's possible you have some pins around the wrong way (i.e. power/ground pins swapped for the led strip)</li>
    <li>Before uploading code to the board, might need to push the reset button on the board first for it to upload successfully</li>
</ul>

<h4>What's next?</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Denser and longer led strip</li>
    <li>Shorter cables</li>
    <li>Short dials/potentiometers</li>
    <li>Use spade connectors where possible instead of soldering</li>
</ul>

